Timestamp: 2026-04-18T23:25:38
Agent: agent
User Input: how to use Log File Highlighter to make agent_log.log look better
Agent output: Use Log File Highlighter with custom patterns tuned to your log format in [lab-3/agent_log.log](lab-3/agent_log.log).

1. Install extension
1. Open Extensions in VS Code.
2. Search for Log File Highlighter (publisher: emilast).
3. Install it.

2. Open settings JSON
1. Open Command Palette.
2. Run Preferences: Open User Settings (JSON).

3. Add this configuration
Paste this into your settings JSON (merge with existing content):

    {
      "files.associations": {
        "*.log": "log",
        "*.log.*": "log"
      },
      "logFileHighlighter.enableProgressIndicator": true,
      "logFileHighlighter.progressIndicatorUnderlineColor": "#2d9cdb",
      "logFileHighlighter.customPatterns": [
        {
          "pattern": "^Timestamp:\\s.*$",
          "foreground": "#6ad1ff",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^Agent:\\s.*$",
          "foreground": "#ffd166",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^User Input:\\s.*$",
          "foreground": "#a0e7e5",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^Agent output:\\s.*$",
          "foreground": "#7bd389",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^Validation:\\s*$",
          "foreground": "#f4a261",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^Current output path is:\\s*$",
          "foreground": "#cdb4db",
          "fontWeight": "bold"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^\\s*-\\s.*passed.*$",
          "patternFlags": "i",
          "foreground": "#7bd389"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "^\\s*-\\s.*(fail|failed|error|exception).*$",
          "patternFlags": "i",
          "foreground": "#ffffff",
          "background": "#c1121f",
          "highlightEntireLine": true,
          "overviewColor": "#c1121f",
          "overviewRulerLane": "Right"
        },
        {
          "pattern": "\\[[^\\]]+\\]\\([^\\)]+\\)",
          "foreground": "#9aa5b1",
          "fontStyle": "italic"
        }
      ],
      "[log]": {
        "editor.largeFileOptimizations": false
      }
    }

4. Reload and verify
1. Reopen [lab-3/agent_log.log](lab-3/agent_log.log).
2. You should now see clear visual separation of headers, validation status, and error-like lines.
3. Select multiple timestamp lines to see duration/progress visualization.

If you want, I can set up a workspace-level [.vscode/settings.json](.vscode/settings.json) for this project so it works immediately for anyone opening this repo.

